==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amidogen
<hw>A*mid"o*gen</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Amide</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A compound radical, <chform>NH2</chform>, not yet obtained in a
separate state, which may be regarded as ammonia from the molecule of
which one of its hydrogen atoms has been removed; -- called also the
<altname>amido group</altname>, and in composition represented by the
form <xex>amido</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amidol</ent>⟦br⟧
